commit.message:
Correctly print uint64_t

%lu will only print 32-bit wide numbers on some platforms (like i386-linux). By casting to unsigned long long and printing %llu we ensure that 64-bits are printed on all platforms.

gphoto2: Use pthread_t abstract type for thead IDs

commit.message:
gphoto2: Use pthread_t abstract type for thead IDs

This is not a plain old datatype in every libc, e.g. with musl this
would fail in type conversion

Signed-off-by: Khem Raj <raj.khem@gmail.com>
fix encoding error with the copyright character

Use modern libtool macros

Use modern libtool macros, which can be helpful for linking gphoto2
against a libgphoto2.la file in non-standard build situtations.

Also do NOT m4_pattern_allow AM_PROG_AR, as allowing it does not
make any sense at all. I vaguely remember some issue related to
AM_PROG_LIBTOOL and AM_PROG_AR from many years ago, but the modern
LT_INIT should have fixed that.

Remove unused and unsafe system(3) based --hook-script implementation

Back in 2006, I wrote a safe execve(3) based alternative implementation
and we have been using that ever since.

I left the old unsafe system(3) based implementation in the source
file #ifdef'ed out just in case someone needed it, but that does not
appear to have happened, so we can get rid of it.

consistent macro arg quoting and indentation

Use consistent macro argument quoting and indentation throughout
configure.ac
